<span class="comment_author"><a href="http://www.freedomfromcreditors.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-commentauthor','http://www.freedomfromcreditors.com']);"  rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Allan Henry</a></span>
<span class="comment_time">June 1, 2011 at 11:46 am</span>

					</dt>
					<dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-1529">
<p>Yes the article may state that New Mexico doesn&#8217;t publish the owners of the New Mexico LLC, However if you understand what it is trying to tell you than you wont care.  The article is trying to tell you that is required to form a New Mexico LLC, is only information required for the Articles of Organization which are:</p>
<p>(1) the name of the company and the address of the principal office.</p>
<p>(2) the name and address of the resident agent, and</p>
<p>(3) the duration of the LLC</p>
<p>No where is it required to have your owners published just the registered agent which you can hire a company to do for you leaving the LLC private in all regards.</p>
</div>
					</dd>
