					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-1655">
<p>&#8220;Hold Valuable Assets – So your 1998 Dodge Neon might not be a prime candidate to put under a New Mexico LLC, unless you loan it to your mother-in-law.  Anything worth more than a few hundred dollars, or a bunch of stuff worth more than a few hundred dollars combined, will be perfect assets to hold in your New Mexico LLC. Things like cars, trucks, trailers, boats, planes, motorcycles, jet-skis, recreational vehicles, houses, real estate, land, rental properties, commercial properties, bank accounts, stocks, bonds, other financial assets, collectibles, equipment, animals, and anything else of value or exposing you to risk.&#8221;</p>
<p>I&#8217;m sold. I want to register my pet rattlesnake in the name of a New Mexico LLC. How do I start?</p>
</div>
