					</dt>
					<dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-1707">
<p>To Greg: It appears one would need to know the name of the LLC in order to do a search- yet, unless I am missing something, the name itself would not be known to outsiders, and could also be protected by layering into another LLC. </p>
<p>To Sophia: My understanding is that an LLC may acquire a tax id number from the IRS (so , not your SS#) and using that number, a bank account may be established.  My understanding (from asking my credit union) is that bank accounts are searched in , say, judgement cases, via the SS# of the account holder, which it is assumed they have&#8230;. but they would not have the new Tax ID #.  </p>
<p>Any comments on this from others?  Am I on the right track here?</p>
</div>
