					<dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-2184">
<p>And to GP- If you are the initial (cash) purchaser of the item to be put right into NM LLC, there might be no way to easily find the LLC name, BUT, if you transfer already-owned items (car,boat, gun, R.E. etc.) that require re-titling or transfer paperwork, THOSE are usually public record, and searchable. Maybe you could sell yours for cash and newly buy someone elses  similar item, but if close in time/location that might also be related by a diligent searcher (after all, if they see it in YOUR driveway, or in the story above, if your aunt rolls over on you!) Put yourself in the searchers shoes. My favorite Gene Hackman line in &#8216;HEIST&#8217; (explaining a plan) &#8220;I try and imagine a guy smarter than me and think&#8221; What would HE  do?&#8221;&#8221;</p>
